  "prompt": "What are the top ten most powerful missiles in the world?",
  "response": "The term \"most powerful\" can be subjective and depends on various factors such as range, payload, accuracy, speed, and technological sophistication. However, here is a list of ten of the most formidable and advanced missiles in the world as of recent years, based on their capabilities and strategic significance:\n\n1. **RS-28 Sarmat (SATAN 2)** - Russia  \n   - Intercontinental Ballistic Missile (ICBM)  \n   - Range: ~18,000 km  \n   - Capable of carrying multiple independently targetable reentry vehicles (MIRVs) and hypersonic gliders.  \n\n2. **LGM-30G Minuteman III** - United States  \n   - ICBM  \n   - Range: ~13,000 km  \n   - A mainstay of the U.S. nuclear triad, known for its reliability and precision.  \n\n3. **DF-41 (Dongfeng-41)** - China  \n   - ICBM  \n   - Range: ~12,000\u201315,000 km  \n   - Can carry multiple MIRVs and is road-mobile, enhancing its survivability.  \n\n4. **Trident II (D5)** - United States/United Kingdom  \n   - Submarine-Launched Ballistic Missile (SLBM)  \n   - Range: ~12,000 km  \n   - Deployed on Ohio-class submarines, it is highly accurate and carries multiple MIRVs.  \n\n5. **SS-18 Satan (R-36M2)** - Russia  \n   - ICBM  \n   - Range: ~16,000 km  \n   - Known for its massive payload capacity and destructive power.  \n\n6. **Kh-47M2 Kinzhal** - Russia  \n   - Air-Launched Ballistic Missile (ALBM)  \n   - Range: ~2,000 km  \n   - Hypersonic speed and maneuverability make it difficult to intercept.  \n\n7. **Agni-V** - India  \n   - ICBM  \n   - Range: ~5,000\u20138,000 km  \n   - Can carry MIRVs and is part of India's nuclear deterrent.  \n\n8. **BrahMos** - India/Russia  \n   - Supersonic Cruise Missile  \n   - Range: ~290\u2013500 km (extended versions in development)  \n   - Known for its speed and precision, used in land, sea, and air variants.  \n\n9. **Tomahawk** - United States  \n   - Cruise Missile  \n   - Range: ~1,600 km  \n   - Highly accurate and widely used in precision strikes.  \n\n10. **Jericho III** - Israel  \n    - ICBM  \n    - Range: ~4,800\u201311,500 km  \n    - Part of Israel's nuclear deterrent, with advanced targeting capabilities.  \n\nThese missiles represent some of the most advanced and strategically significant weapons systems in the world, highlighting the capabilities of their respective nations. Note that this list is based on publicly available information and may not include classified or developmental systems.",
